The paper discusses the construction of bibliometric networks, which involves analyzing data related to publications and authors. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), software engineering (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, since the paper focuses on analyzing networks and their properties, we believe that cs.DL and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.SD, and cs.CY.
